checked exceptions - -
This are caught at compile time 
These are significant errors which can be handled , so that execution will be smooth
This occurs during input mismatch or conditions not matching the program
Exceptions are anticipated
These include file exception

unchecked exceptions - -
This are not caught at compile time
Execution will not be smooth
This occurs during the programming errors
Exceptions will occur but are not anticipated by the user
These include arithmetic, array out of index exceptions